    "We should invite children to approach computing and its consequences critically and to shape the trajectories of computing of the future.",
    "Moreover, we should invite children to view the world and the crises within with a critical yet constructive stance, trying to make the world a better place for us all.",
    "Naturally, computing alone can never solve complex societal problems, but it can contribute on its part.",
    "We report on a design research project in which we explored critical, ethical and empowering design methods together with children.",
    "The methods, in different ways, invite critique of the status quo with injustice, inequality and oppression; and taking action to transform it (Iivari et al. 2022)."
